metadata.name: EZ_TOKEN_TRANSFERS
metadata.comment: This table will contain all events in the ```fact_token_transfers table```, along with joined columns such as token price, symbol, and decimals where possible that allow for easier analysis of token transfer events. Please note Native ETH transfers are not included here.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This will not be unique in this table as a transaction could include multiple transfer events.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of this transaction.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The from address at the transaction level.

ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The to address at the transaction level.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: Contract address of the token being transferred.

FROM_ADDRESS.name: FROM_ADDRESS
FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The sending address of this transfer.

TO_ADDRESS.name: TO_ADDRESS
TO_ADDRESS.comment: The receiving address of this transfer. This can be a contract address.

RAW_AMOUNT.name: RAW_AMOUNT
RAW_AMOUNT.comment: The amount of tokens transferred. This value is not decimal adjusted.

DECIMALS.name: DECIMALS
DECIMALS.comment: The number of decimal places this contract needs adjusted where token values exist. For example, use the decimal field to correctly transform raw amounts in ```fact_token_transfers```.

SYMBOL.name: SYMBOL
SYMBOL.comment: The symbol used to represent this contract. Please note this is not necessarily unique.

TOKEN_PRICE.name: TOKEN_PRICE
TOKEN_PRICE.comment: The price, if available, for this token at the transfer time.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The decimal transformed amount for this token. Tokens without a decimal adjustment will be nulled out here.

AMOUNT_USD.name: AMOUNT_USD
AMOUNT_USD.comment: The amount in US dollars for this transfer at the time of the transfer. Tokens without a decimal adjustment or price will be nulled out here.

HAS_DECIMAL.name: HAS_DECIMAL
HAS_DECIMAL.comment: Whether or not our contracts model contains the necessary decimal adjustment for this token.

HAS_PRICE.name: HAS_PRICE
HAS_PRICE.comment: Whether or not our prices model contains this hourly token price.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the transfer event occurred. This field can be used to find more details on the event within the ```fact_event_logs``` table.

metadata.name: EZ_NFT_MINTS
metadata.comment: This table contains NFT mint events, defined as an NFT transfers from a burn address to an address, on the ethereum blockchain.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The block timestamp at which the NFT event occurred.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: The block number at which the NFT event occurred.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: The transaction hash for the NFT event. This is not necessarily unique in this table as a transaction may contain multiple NFT events.

EVENT_TYPE.name: EVENT_TYPE
EVENT_TYPE.comment: The type of NFT event in this transaction, either `sale`,  `bid_won` or `redeem`.

NFT_ADDRESS.name: NFT_ADDRESS
NFT_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the NFT.

PROJECT_NAME.name: PROJECT_NAME
PROJECT_NAME.comment: The name of the NFT project. This field, along with metadata, will be filled in over time.

NFT_FROM_ADDRESS.name: NFT_FROM_ADDRESS
NFT_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The sending address of the NFT in the transaction.

NFT_TO_ADDRESS.name: NFT_TO_ADDRESS
NFT_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The receiving address of the NFT in the transaction.

TOKENID.name: TOKENID
TOKENID.comment: The token ID for this NFT contract.

TOKEN_METADATA.name: TOKEN_METADATA
TOKEN_METADATA.comment: The token metadata for this NFT. This may be blank for many NFTs. We are working to expand this field.

ERC1155_VALUE.name: ERC1155_VALUE
ERC1155_VALUE.comment: If the NFT is an ERC-1155 contract, this field may be one or greater, representing the number of tokens.

MINT_PRICE_ETH.name: MINT_PRICE_ETH
MINT_PRICE_ETH.comment: The price paid in ETH to mint the NFT(s).

MINT_PRICE_USD.name: MINT_PRICE_USD
MINT_PRICE_USD.comment: The price paid in US dollars to mint the NFT(s).

NFT_COUNT.name: NFT_COUNT
NFT_COUNT.comment: The number of NFTs minted in this event.

MINT_PRICE_TOKENS.name: MINT_PRICE_TOKENS
MINT_PRICE_TOKENS.comment: The decimal adjusted amount of tokens supplied within the same transaction to mint the NFT. This field may not handle all edge cases.

MINT_PRICE_TOKENS_USD.name: MINT_PRICE_TOKENS_USD
MINT_PRICE_TOKENS_USD.comment: The amount of tokens supplied in US dollars within the same transaction to mint the NFT. This field may not handle all edge cases.

MINT_TOKEN_SYMBOL.name: MINT_TOKEN_SYMBOL
MINT_TOKEN_SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of the token supplied to mint the NFT, if applicable. This field may not handle all edge cases.

MINT_TOKEN_ADDRESS.name: MINT_TOKEN_ADDRESS
MINT_TOKEN_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the token supplied to mint the NFT, if applicable. This field may not handle all edge cases.

TX_FEE.name: TX_FEE
TX_FEE.comment: The gas fee for this transaction in ETH.

metadata.name: EZ_NFT_SALES
metadata.comment: This table contains NFT events on the Ethereum blockchain. It currently supports sales on Opensea, Seaport, LooksRare, Rarible, x2y2, and NFTX. More data and exchanges will be added over time.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: The block number at which the NFT event occurred.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The block timestamp at which the NFT event occurred.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: The transaction hash for the NFT event. This is not necessarily unique in this table as a transaction may contain multiple NFT events.

EVENT_TYPE.name: EVENT_TYPE
EVENT_TYPE.comment: The type of NFT event in this transaction, either `sale`,  `bid_won` or `redeem`.

PLATFORM_ADDRESS.name: PLATFORM_ADDRESS
PLATFORM_ADDRESS.comment: The address of the exchange used for the transaction.

PLATFORM_NAME.name: PLATFORM_NAME
PLATFORM_NAME.comment: The name of the exchange used for the trade. Currently, the exchanges supported are `opensea`, `looksrare`, `rarible`, `x2y2`, and `nftx`. More exchanges will be added over time.

PLATFORM_EXCHANGE_VERSION.name: PLATFORM_EXCHANGE_VERSION
PLATFORM_EXCHANGE_VERSION.comment: The version of the exchange contract used for the transaction.

SELLER_ADDRESS.name: SELLER_ADDRESS
SELLER_ADDRESS.comment: The address of the seller of the NFT in the transaction.

BUYER_ADDRESS.name: BUYER_ADDRESS
BUYER_ADDRESS.comment: The address of the buyer of the NFT in the transaction.

NFT_ADDRESS.name: NFT_ADDRESS
NFT_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the NFT.

PROJECT_NAME.name: PROJECT_NAME
PROJECT_NAME.comment: The name of the NFT project. This field, along with metadata, will be filled in over time.

ERC1155_VALUE.name: ERC1155_VALUE
ERC1155_VALUE.comment: If the NFT is an ERC-1155 contract, this field may be one or greater, representing the number of tokens.

TOKENID.name: TOKENID
TOKENID.comment: The token ID for this NFT contract.

TOKEN_METADATA.name: TOKEN_METADATA
TOKEN_METADATA.comment: The token metadata for this NFT. This may be blank for many NFTs. We are working to expand this field.

CURRENCY_SYMBOL.name: CURRENCY_SYMBOL
CURRENCY_SYMBOL.comment: The token symbol for this NFT event.

CURRENCY_ADDRESS.name: CURRENCY_ADDRESS
CURRENCY_ADDRESS.comment: The token contract address for this NFT event. This will be `ETH` for native ETH transactions.

PRICE.name: PRICE
PRICE.comment: The amount of the NFT event in the currency in which the transaction occurred, decimal adjusted where possible.

PRICE_USD.name: PRICE_USD
PRICE_USD.comment: The amount of the NFT event in US dollars. This will be null for tokens without a decimal adjustment or hourly price.

TOTAL_FEES.name: TOTAL_FEES
TOTAL_FEES.comment: The total amount of fees paid relating to the NFT purchase in the transaction currency. This includes royalty payments to creators and platform fees. Please note, this does not include the gas fee.

PLATFORM_FEE.name: PLATFORM_FEE
PLATFORM_FEE.comment: The decimal adjusted amount of fees paid to the platform for this NFT event in the transaction's currency. For Opensea, we assume a 2.5% fee on all marketplace purchases, per their docs. Private sales do not have platform or creator fees on Opensea.

CREATOR_FEE.name: CREATOR_FEE
CREATOR_FEE.comment: The decimal adjusted amount of fees paid to the NFT collection as royalty payments for this NFT event in the transaction's currency. For Opensea, this is the difference between the total fees paid and a 2.5% Opensea platform fee.

TOTAL_FEES_USD.name: TOTAL_FEES_USD
TOTAL_FEES_USD.comment: The total amount of fees paid relating to the NFT purchase in US dollars. This includes royalty payments to creators and platform fees. Please note, this does not include the gas fee.

PLATFORM_FEE_USD.name: PLATFORM_FEE_USD
PLATFORM_FEE_USD.comment: The amount of fees paid to the platform for this NFT event in US dollars. For Opensea, we assume a 2.5% fee on all marketplace purchases, per their docs. Private sales do not have platform or creator fees on Opensea.

CREATOR_FEE_USD.name: CREATOR_FEE_USD
CREATOR_FEE_USD.comment: The amount of fees paid to the NFT collection as royalty payments for this NFT event in US dollars. For Opensea, this is the difference between the total fees paid and a 2.5% Opensea platform fee.

TX_FEE.name: TX_FEE
TX_FEE.comment: The gas fee for this transaction in ETH.

TX_FEE_USD.name: TX_FEE_USD
TX_FEE_USD.comment: The gas fee for this transaction in US dollars.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The from address of this transaction. In most cases, this is the NFT buyer. However, for some more complex transactions, it may not be the NFT buyer.

ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The to address of this transaction. In most cases, this is the exchange contract. However, for some more complex NFT events, such as aggregate buys with tools such as Gem and Genie, this may not be the exchange address.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of this transaction.

has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: The transaction hash for the NFT event. This is not necessarily unique in this table as a transaction may contain multiple NFT events.

EVENT_TYPE.name: EVENT_TYPE
EVENT_TYPE.comment: The type of NFT event in this transaction, either `sale`,  `bid_won` or `redeem`.

NFT_ADDRESS.name: NFT_ADDRESS
NFT_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the NFT.

PROJECT_NAME.name: PROJECT_NAME
PROJECT_NAME.comment: The name of the NFT project. This field, along with metadata, will be filled in over time.

NFT_FROM_ADDRESS.name: NFT_FROM_ADDRESS
NFT_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The sending address of the NFT in the transaction.

NFT_TO_ADDRESS.name: NFT_TO_ADDRESS
NFT_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The receiving address of the NFT in the transaction.

TOKENID.name: TOKENID
TOKENID.comment: The token ID for this NFT contract.

TOKEN_METADATA.name: TOKEN_METADATA
TOKEN_METADATA.comment: The token metadata for this NFT. This may be blank for many NFTs. We are working to expand this field.

ERC1155_VALUE.name: ERC1155_VALUE
ERC1155_VALUE.comment: If the NFT is an ERC-1155 contract, this field may be one or greater, representing the number of tokens.

has_stats.label: Has Stats?
has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table

metadata.name: DIM_CONTRACTS
metadata.comment: This table contains contract details for contracts deployed on the Ethereum blockchain.

ADDRESS.name: ADDRESS
ADDRESS.comment: The unique Ethereum address of the deployed contract.

SYMBOL.name: SYMBOL
SYMBOL.comment: The symbol used to represent this contract. Please note this is not necessarily unique.

NAME.name: NAME
NAME.comment: The name of the deployed contract. Please note this is not necessarily unique.

DECIMALS.name: DECIMALS
DECIMALS.comment: The number of decimal places this contract needs adjusted where token values exist. For example, use the decimal field to correctly transform raw amounts in ```fact_token_transfers```.

CONTRACT_METADATA.name: CONTRACT_METADATA
CONTRACT_METADATA.comment: This JSON column contains other relevant details for each contract.

has_stats.label: Has Stats?
has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table

metadata.name: FACT_BLOCKS
metadata.comment: This table contains block level data for the Ethereum Blockchain. This table can be used to analyze trends at a block level, for example gas fees vs. total transactions over time. For more information, please see [Etherscan Resources](https://etherscan.io/directory/Learning_Resources/Ethereum) or [The Ethereum Organization](https://ethereum.org/en/developers/docs/blocks/)

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

NETWORK.name: NETWORK
NETWORK.comment: The network on the blockchain used by a transaction.

BLOCKCHAIN.name: BLOCKCHAIN
BLOCKCHAIN.comment: The blockchain on which transactions are being confirmed.

TX_COUNT.name: TX_COUNT
TX_COUNT.comment: Total number of transactions within a block.

DIFFICULTY.name: DIFFICULTY
DIFFICULTY.comment: The effort required to mine the block.

TOTAL_DIFFICULTY.name: TOTAL_DIFFICULTY
TOTAL_DIFFICULTY.comment: Total difficulty of the chain at a given block.

EXTRA_DATA.name: EXTRA_DATA
EXTRA_DATA.comment: Any data included by the miner for a given block.

GAS_LIMIT.name: GAS_LIMIT
GAS_LIMIT.comment: Total gas limit provided by all transactions in the block.

GAS_USED.name: GAS_USED
GAS_USED.comment: Total gas used in the block.

HASH.name: HASH
HASH.comment: The hash of the block header for a given block.

PARENT_HASH.name: PARENT_HASH
PARENT_HASH.comment: The hash of the block from which a given block is generated. Also known as the parent block.

MINER.name: MINER
MINER.comment: Miner who successfully added a given block to the blockchain.

NONCE.name: NONCE
NONCE.comment: Block nonce is a value used during mining to demonstrate proof of work for a given block.

RECEIPTS_ROOT.name: RECEIPTS_ROOT
RECEIPTS_ROOT.comment: The root of the state trie.

SHA3_UNCLES.name: SHA3_UNCLES
SHA3_UNCLES.comment: The mechanism which Ethereum Javascript RLP encodes an empty string.

SIZE.name: SIZE
SIZE.comment: Block size, which is determined by a given block's gas limit.

UNCLE_BLOCKS.name: UNCLE_BLOCKS
UNCLE_BLOCKS.comment: Uncle blocks occur when two blocks are mined and broadcasted at the same time, with the same block number. The block validated across the most nodes will be added to the primary chain, and the other one becomes an uncle block. Miners do receive rewards for uncle blocks.

BLOCK_HEADER_JSON.name: BLOCK_HEADER_JSON
BLOCK_HEADER_JSON.comment: This JSON column contains the block header details.

has_stats.label: Has Stats?
has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table

metadata.name: FACT_EVENT_LOGS
metadata.comment: This table contains flattened event logs from transactions on the Ethereum Blockchain. Transactions may have multiple events, which are denoted by the event index for a transaction hash. Therefore, this table is unique on the combination of transaction hash and event index. Event names are decoded in this table where possible. The event inputs column will contain the log details in JSON format. Specific fields can be pulled from this column using the following sample format: ```event_inputs:<FILED_NAME>::<DATA TYPE> as <FIELD_NAME>```.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This field will not be unique in this table, as a given transaction can include multiple events.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of this transaction.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The from address at the transaction level.

ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The to address at the transaction level.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: The address interacted with for a given event.

CONTRACT_NAME.name: CONTRACT_NAME
CONTRACT_NAME.comment: The name of the contract or token, where possible.

EVENT_NAME.name: EVENT_NAME
EVENT_NAME.comment: The decoded event name for a given event.

EVENT_INPUTS.name: EVENT_INPUTS
EVENT_INPUTS.comment: The decoded event inputs for a given event.

EVENT_REMOVED.name: EVENT_REMOVED
EVENT_REMOVED.comment: Whether the event has been removed from the transaction.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the event occurred. This field can be used within other event based tables such as ```fact_transfers``` & ```ez_token_transfers```.

has_stats.label: Has Stats?
has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table

has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table

metadata.name: FACT_TOKEN_TRANSFERS
metadata.comment: This table contains events on the Ethereum Blockchain with an event name of 'Transfer'. The contract address is the token transferred, and the raw amount field is the amount of tokens transferred. Please note this amount is not decimal adjusted. Decimal adjustments for a token address can be found in ```dim_contracts```. This table will not contain transfers of native ETH.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This will not be unique in this table as a transaction could include multiple transfer events.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of this transaction.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The from address at the transaction level.

ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The to address at the transaction level.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: Contract address of the token being transferred.

FROM_ADDRESS.name: FROM_ADDRESS
FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The sending address of this transfer.

TO_ADDRESS.name: TO_ADDRESS
TO_ADDRESS.comment: The receiving address of this transfer. This can be a contract address.

RAW_AMOUNT.name: RAW_AMOUNT
RAW_AMOUNT.comment: The amount of tokens transferred. This value is not decimal adjusted.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the transfer event occurred. This field can be used to find more details on the event within the ```fact_event_logs``` table.

has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table

metadata.name: EZ_SWAPS
metadata.comment:
This table will contain all swap events done on the Sushiswap platform in the ```fact_event_logs table```, joined along with the addresses of both tokens in the swap and the decimal adjusted prices.
Note: A rule has been put in place to null out the amount_USD if that number is too divergent between amount_in_USD and amount_out_usd. This can happen for swaps of less liquid tokens during very high fluctuation of price.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This field will not be unique in this table, as a given transaction can include multiple events.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of this transaction.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS

ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: The address interacted with for a given event.

EVENT_NAME.name: EVENT_NAME

AMOUNT_IN.name: AMOUNT_IN
AMOUNT_IN.comment: The amount of tokens put into the swap.

AMOUNT_OUT.name: AMOUNT_OUT
AMOUNT_OUT.comment: The amount of tokens taken out of or received from the swap.

SENDER.name: SENDER
SENDER.comment: The Router is the Sender in the swap function.

TX_TO.name: TX_TO
TX_TO.comment: The tx_to is the address who receives the swapped token. This corresponds to the "to" field in the swap function.

PLATFORM.name: PLATFORM
PLATFORM.comment: This field denotes which application the liquidity pool belongs to.

TOKEN_IN.name: TOKEN_IN
TOKEN_IN.comment: The address of the token sent for swap.

TOKEN_OUT.name: TOKEN_OUT
TOKEN_OUT.comment: The address of the token being swapped to.

SYMBOL_IN.name: SYMBOL_IN
SYMBOL_IN.comment: The symbol of the token sent for swap.

SYMBOL_OUT.name: SYMBOL_OUT
SYMBOL_OUT.comment: The symbol of the token being swapped to.

AMOUNT_IN_USD.name: AMOUNT_IN_USD
AMOUNT_IN_USD.comment: The amount of tokens put into the swap converted to USD using the price of the token.

AMOUNT_OUT_USD.name: AMOUNT_OUT_USD
AMOUNT_OUT_USD.comment: The amount of tokens taken out of or received from the swap converted to USD using the price of the token.

metadata.name: FACT_TRANSACTIONS
metadata.comment: This table contains transaction level data for the Ethereum Blockchain. Each transaction will have a unique transaction hash, along with transactions fees and an ETH value transferred when applicable. Transactions may be native ETH transfers or interactions with contract addresses. For more information, please see [The Ethereum Organization - Transactions](https://ethereum.org/en/developers/docs/transactions/)

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

BLOCK_HASH.name: BLOCK_HASH
BLOCK_HASH.comment: Block hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generate when a block is produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed.

NONCE.name: NONCE
NONCE.comment: The number of transactions sent from a given address.

POSITION.name: POSITION
POSITION.comment: The position of the transaction within the block.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of the contract call.

FROM_ADDRESS.name: FROM_ADDRESS
FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The sending address of this transaction.

TO_ADDRESS.name: TO_ADDRESS
TO_ADDRESS.comment: The receiving address of this transaction. This can be a contract address.

TX_FEE.name: TX_FEE
TX_FEE.comment: Amount paid to validate the transaction in Ether.

GAS_PRICE.name: GAS_PRICE
GAS_PRICE.comment: Cost per unit of gas in Gwei.

GAS_LIMIT.name: GAS_LIMIT
GAS_LIMIT.comment: Maximum amount of gas allocated for the transaction.

CUMULATIVE_GAS_USED.name: CUMULATIVE_GAS_USED
CUMULATIVE_GAS_USED.comment: The total amount of gas used when this transaction was executed in the block.

INPUT_DATA.name: INPUT_DATA
INPUT_DATA.comment: This column contains additional data for this transaction, and is commonly used as part of a contract interaction or as a message to the recipient.

TX_JSON.name: TX_JSON
TX_JSON.comment: This JSON column contains the transaction details, including event logs.

has_stats.label: Has Stats?
has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table

metadata.name: FACT_TRACES
metadata.comment: This table contains flattened trace data for internal contract calls on the Ethereum blockchain. Hex encoded fields can be decoded to integers by using `TO_NUMBER(<FIELD>, 'XXXXXXXXXXXX')`, with the number of Xs being the max length of the encoded field. You must also remove the `0x` from your field to use the `TO_NUMBER()` function, if applicable.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: The transaction hash for the trace. Please note, this is not necessarily unique in this table as transactions frequently have multiple traces.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: The block number of this transaction.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The block timestamp of this transaction.

FROM_ADDRESS.name: FROM_ADDRESS
FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The sending address of this trace. This is not necessarily the from address of the transaction.

TO_ADDRESS.name: TO_ADDRESS
TO_ADDRESS.comment: The receiving address of this trace. This is not necessarily the to address of the transaction.

ETH_VALUE.name: ETH_VALUE
ETH_VALUE.comment: The amount of ETH transferred in this trace.

GAS.name: GAS
GAS.comment: The gas supplied for this trace.

GAS_USED.name: GAS_USED
GAS_USED.comment: The gas used for this trace.

INPUT.name: INPUT
INPUT.comment: The input data for this trace.

OUTPUT.name: OUTPUT
OUTPUT.comment: The output data for this trace.

TYPE.name: TYPE
TYPE.comment: The type of internal transaction. Common trace types are `CALL`, `DELEGATECALL`, and `STATICCALL`.

IDENTIFIER.name: IDENTIFIER
IDENTIFIER.comment: This field represents the position and type of the trace within the transaction.

DATA.name: DATA
DATA.comment: The raw JSON data for this trace.

SUB_TRACES.name: SUB_TRACES
SUB_TRACES.comment: The amount of nested sub traces for this trace.

has_stats.label: Has Stats?
has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table
